Description: Sherd of rim and rotelle of large East Greek pottery oinochoe; cream slip; much worn. Exterior glazed; interior reserved between rotelles; inner side of rotelle worn, but probably glazed; outside has plastic nipple at centre and rosette around; some petals red.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.765)
